text_answer.content: Is there an order to the questions.  It does not appear that way.  Question one focuses on only pargraph 3.  It appears to be asking about details.  Question 2 seems to also be about a detail from the text.  Question 3 wants students to connect both passages about what they have in common.  Questions 4 & 5 are inference questions, but these are not being rated.  The directions in the Mind Map directs the student to arrange the boxes vertically, but they are also arranged horizontally.  The writing rubric helps the students know what traits are being assessed, but the traits at times outnumber the points allotted.  For example,  the mechanical traits seem to be an all or nothing in the sense that 1 mistake receives the same points as a text that me multiple error in this area.

text_answer.content: I misinterpreted the rubrin when rating the previous passage.  I suggest listing the major category and the points alotted in parentheses, followed by the trait .  For example, List the category and points.  On the next line, list the first trait and points.  On the next line, list the next trait and points, etc.  Written as a paragraph has too many numbers and categories all blended together.
